{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":760,"text":"On January 26, 2013,"},{"time":3480,"text":"a band of al-Qaeda militants\nentered the ancient city of Timbuktu"},{"time":7000,"text":"on the southern edge of the Sahara Desert."},{"time":9640,"text":"There, they set fire to a medieval library\nof 30,000 manuscripts"},{"time":14280,"text":"written in Arabic\nand several African languages"},{"time":17080,"text":"and ranging in subject from astronomy\nto geography, history to medicine,"},{"time":22840,"text":"including one book which records"},{"time":24560,"text":"perhaps the first treatment\nfor male erectile dysfunction."},{"time":29760,"text":"Unknown in the West,"},{"time":31080,"text":"this was the collected wisdom\nof an entire continent,"},{"time":34520,"text":"the voice of Africa at a time when Africa\nwas thought not to have a voice at all."},{"time":39480,"text":"The mayor of Bamako,\nwho witnessed the event,"},{"time":42000,"text":"called the burning of the manuscripts"},{"time":43960,"text":"\"a crime against world cultural heritage.\""},{"time":46880,"text":"And he was right --"},{"time":48440,"text":"or he would have been, if it weren't\nfor the fact that he was also lying."}]},{"cues":[{"time":52560,"text":"In fact, just before,"},{"time":55320,"text":"African scholars had collected\na random assortment of old books"},{"time":59480,"text":"and left them out\nfor the terrorists to burn."},{"time":62000,"text":"Today, the collection\nlies hidden in Bamako,"},{"time":64959,"text":"the capital of Mali,"},{"time":66360,"text":"moldering in the high humidity."},{"time":68480,"text":"What was rescued by ruse"},{"time":70360,"text":"is now once again in jeopardy,"},{"time":72120,"text":"this time by climate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":74200,"text":"But Africa, and the far-flung\ncorners of the world,"},{"time":76640,"text":"are not the only places,\nor even the main places"},{"time":78960,"text":"in which manuscripts that could change\nthe history of world culture"},{"time":83280,"text":"are in jeopardy."},{"time":85920,"text":"Several years ago, I conducted\na survey of European research libraries"},{"time":90680,"text":"and discovered that,\nat the barest minimum,"},{"time":92960,"text":"there are 60,000 manuscripts"},{"time":96200,"text":"pre-1500"},{"time":97840,"text":"that are illegible\nbecause of water damage,"},{"time":100800,"text":"fading, mold and chemical reagents."},{"time":104800,"text":"The real number is likely double that,"},{"time":107800,"text":"and that doesn't even count"},{"time":110000,"text":"Renaissance manuscripts\nand modern manuscripts"},{"time":112640,"text":"and cultural heritage\nobjects such as maps."}]},{"cues":[{"time":117960,"text":"What if there were a technology"},{"time":120440,"text":"that could recover\nthese lost and unknown works?"},{"time":125800,"text":"Imagine worldwide\nhow a trove of hundreds of thousands"},{"time":130240,"text":"of previously unknown texts"},{"time":133200,"text":"could radically transform\nour knowledge of the past."},{"time":138280,"text":"Imagine what unknown classics\nwe would discover"},{"time":142320,"text":"which would rewrite the canons\nof literature, history,"},{"time":145680,"text":"philosophy, music --"},{"time":147840,"text":"or, more provocatively, that could\nrewrite our cultural identities,"},{"time":151400,"text":"building new bridges\nbetween people and culture."},{"time":155520,"text":"These are the questions\nthat transformed me"},{"time":158080,"text":"from a medieval scholar,\na reader of texts,"},{"time":160920,"text":"into a textual scientist."}]},{"cues":[{"time":164120,"text":"What an unsatisfying word \"reader\" is."},{"time":166440,"text":"For me, it conjures up\nimages of passivity,"},{"time":169040,"text":"of someone sitting idly in an armchair"},{"time":171480,"text":"waiting for knowledge to come to him"},{"time":173800,"text":"in a neat little parcel."},{"time":175520,"text":"How much better to be\na participant in the past,"},{"time":178560,"text":"an adventurer in an undiscovered country,"},{"time":181760,"text":"searching for the hidden text."},{"time":185360,"text":"As an academic, I was a mere reader."},{"time":188560,"text":"I read and taught the same classics"},{"time":191000,"text":"that people had been reading\nand teaching for hundreds of years --"},{"time":194160,"text":"Virgil, Ovid, Chaucer, Petrarch --"},{"time":197200,"text":"and with every scholarly article\nthat I published"},{"time":199560,"text":"I added to human knowledge\nin ever-diminishing slivers of insight."},{"time":204760,"text":"What I wanted to be"},{"time":206360,"text":"was an archaeologist of the past,"},{"time":208480,"text":"a discoverer of literature,"},{"time":210080,"text":"an Indiana Jones without the whip --"},{"time":212000,"text":"or, actually, with the whip."}]},{"cues":[{"time":213520,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":214760,"text":"And I wanted it not just for myself\nbut I wanted it for my students as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":218480,"text":"And so six years ago,\nI changed the direction of my career."},{"time":222400,"text":"At the time, I was working\non \"The Chess of Love,\""},{"time":225440,"text":"the last important long poem\nof the European Middle Ages"},{"time":228320,"text":"never to have been edited."},{"time":229960,"text":"And it wasn't edited because\nit existed in only one manuscript"},{"time":233000,"text":"which was so badly damaged\nduring the firebombing of Dresden"},{"time":236280,"text":"in World War II"},{"time":237520,"text":"that generations of scholars\nhad pronounced it lost."},{"time":241400,"text":"For five years, I had been working\nwith an ultraviolet lamp"},{"time":244880,"text":"trying to recover traces of the writing"},{"time":246800,"text":"and I'd gone about as far\nas technology at the time"},{"time":249240,"text":"could actually take me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":250640,"text":"And so I did what many people do."},{"time":252760,"text":"I went online,"},{"time":254800,"text":"and there I learned about"},{"time":256560,"text":"how multispectral imaging had been used\nto recover two lost treatises"},{"time":261160,"text":"of the famed Greek\nmathematician Archimedes"},{"time":264080,"text":"from a 13th-century palimpsest."},{"time":265640,"text":"A palimpsest is a manuscript\nwhich has been erased and overwritten."}]},{"cues":[{"time":270200,"text":"And so, out of the blue,"},{"time":271480,"text":"I decided to write\nto the lead imaging scientist"},{"time":274560,"text":"on the Archimedes palimpsest project,"},{"time":276800,"text":"Professor Roger Easton,"},{"time":278320,"text":"with a plan and a plea."},{"time":280160,"text":"And to my surprise,\nhe actually wrote back."},{"time":284000,"text":"With his help, I was able\nto win a grant from the US government"},{"time":287680,"text":"to build a transportable,\nmultispectral imaging lab,"},{"time":291720,"text":"And with this lab, I transformed\nwhat was a charred and faded mess"},{"time":296560,"text":"into a new medieval classic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":299360,"text":"So how does multispectral\nimaging actually work?"},{"time":302160,"text":"Well, the idea\nbehind multispectral imaging"},{"time":304640,"text":"is something that anyone who is familiar\nwith infrared night vision goggles"},{"time":308960,"text":"will immediately appreciate:"},{"time":310360,"text":"that what we can see\nin the visible spectrum of light"},{"time":312880,"text":"is only a tiny fraction\nof what's actually there."},{"time":315720,"text":"The same is true with invisible writing."},{"time":319280,"text":"Our system uses 12 wavelengths of light"},{"time":323480,"text":"between the ultraviolet and the infrared,"},{"time":326000,"text":"and these are shown down\nonto the manuscript from above"},{"time":329080,"text":"from banks of LEDs,"},{"time":330720,"text":"and another multispectral light source"},{"time":332600,"text":"which comes up through\nthe individual leaves of the manuscript."},{"time":335577,"text":"Up to 35 images per sequence\nper leaf are imaged this way"},{"time":340120,"text":"using a high-powered digital camera\nequipped with a lens"},{"time":342764,"text":"which is made out of quartz."},{"time":344760,"text":"There are about five\nof these in the world."},{"time":346880,"text":"And once we capture these images,"},{"time":348720,"text":"we feed them through\nstatistical algorithms"},{"time":350800,"text":"to further enhance and clarify them,"},{"time":353320,"text":"using software which was originally\ndesigned for satellite images"},{"time":356720,"text":"and used by people\nlike geospatial scientists"},{"time":360120,"text":"and the CIA."}]},{"cues":[{"time":362040,"text":"The results can be spectacular."},{"time":364360,"text":"You may already have heard\nof what's been done"},{"time":366560,"text":"for the Dead Sea Scrolls,"},{"time":367960,"text":"which are slowly gelatinizing."},{"time":370480,"text":"Using infrared, we've been able\nto read even the darkest corners"},{"time":374160,"text":"of the Dead Sea Scrolls."},{"time":376880,"text":"You may not be aware, however,"},{"time":378360,"text":"of other Biblical texts\nthat are in jeopardy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":381120,"text":"Here, for example,\nis a leaf from a manuscript"},{"time":384560,"text":"that we imaged,"},{"time":386360,"text":"which is perhaps the most valuable\nChristian Bible in the world."},{"time":390880,"text":"The Codex Vercellensis is the oldest\ntranslation of the Gospels into Latin,"},{"time":396680,"text":"and it dates from the first half\nof the fourth century."},{"time":400560,"text":"This is the closest we can come"},{"time":402840,"text":"to the Bible at the time\nof the foundation of Christendom"},{"time":406800,"text":"under Emperor Constantine,"},{"time":408440,"text":"and at the time also\nof the Council of Nicaea,"},{"time":411000,"text":"when the basic creed of Christianity\nwas being agreed upon."},{"time":414520,"text":"This manuscript, unfortunately,\nhas been very badly damaged,"},{"time":417800,"text":"and it's damaged because for centuries"},{"time":420040,"text":"it had been used and handled"},{"time":422520,"text":"in swearing in ceremonies in the church."},{"time":425240,"text":"In fact, that purple splotch\nthat you see in the upper left hand corner"},{"time":429920,"text":"is Aspergillus, which is a fungus"},{"time":434240,"text":"which originates in the unwashed hands"},{"time":437800,"text":"of a person with tuberculosis."},{"time":440640,"text":"Our imaging has enabled me\nto make the first transcription"},{"time":443720,"text":"of this manuscript in 250 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":447800,"text":"Having a lab that can travel\nto collections where it's needed, however,"},{"time":451280,"text":"is only part of the solution."},{"time":453480,"text":"The technology is expensive and very rare,"},{"time":456360,"text":"and the imaging and image\nprocessing skills are esoteric."},{"time":459600,"text":"That means that mounting recoveries"},{"time":461320,"text":"is beyond the reach of most researchers\nand all but the wealthiest institutions."},{"time":466240,"text":"That's why I founded the Lazarus Project,"},{"time":469040,"text":"a not-for-profit initiative"},{"time":470720,"text":"to bring multispectral imaging\nto individual researchers"},{"time":474720,"text":"and smaller institutions\nat little or no cost whatsoever."},{"time":479560,"text":"Over the past five years,"},{"time":481200,"text":"our team of imaging scientists,\nscholars and students"},{"time":485080,"text":"has travelled to seven different countries"},{"time":487280,"text":"and have recovered some of the world's\nmost valuable damaged manuscripts,"},{"time":491160,"text":"included the Vercelli Book,\nwhich is the oldest book of English,"},{"time":494184,"text":"the Black Book of Carmarthen,\nthe oldest book of Welsh,"},{"time":496824,"text":"and some of the most valuable\nearliest Gospels"},{"time":500320,"text":"located in what is now\nthe former Soviet Georgia."}]},{"cues":[{"time":504600,"text":"So, spectral imaging\ncan recover lost texts."},{"time":508360,"text":"More subtly, though, it can recover\na second story behind every object,"},{"time":513480,"text":"the story of how, when\nand by whom a text was created,"},{"time":518200,"text":"and, sometimes, what the author\nwas thinking at the time he wrote."},{"time":522600,"text":"Take, for example, a draft\nof the Declaration of Independence"},{"time":525720,"text":"written in Thomas Jefferson's own hand,"},{"time":528160,"text":"which some colleagues of mine\nimaged a few years ago"},{"time":530613,"text":"at the Library of Congress."},{"time":532360,"text":"Curators had noticed\nthat one word throughout"},{"time":535080,"text":"had been scratched out and overwritten."},{"time":537480,"text":"The word overwritten was \"citizens.\""},{"time":540240,"text":"Perhaps you can guess\nwhat the word underneath was."},{"time":543960,"text":"\"Subjects.\""},{"time":545400,"text":"There, ladies and gentlemen,\nis American democracy"},{"time":548240,"text":"evolving under the hand\nof Thomas Jefferson."}]},{"cues":[{"time":551360,"text":"Or consider the 1491 Martellus Map,"},{"time":555240,"text":"which we imaged\nat Yale's Beinecke Library."},{"time":557600,"text":"This was the map\nthat Columbus likely consulted"},{"time":560080,"text":"before he traveled to the New World"},{"time":561800,"text":"and which gave him his idea\nof what Asia looked like"},{"time":564560,"text":"and where Japan was located."},{"time":567640,"text":"The problem with this map\nis that its inks and pigments"},{"time":570680,"text":"had so degraded over time"},{"time":572800,"text":"that this large, nearly seven-foot map,"},{"time":574960,"text":"made the world look like a giant desert."},{"time":577520,"text":"Until now, we had very little idea,\ndetailed idea, that is,"},{"time":581160,"text":"of what Columbus knew of the world"},{"time":582840,"text":"and how world cultures were represented."},{"time":585240,"text":"The main legend of the map\nwas entirely illegible under normal light."},{"time":589400,"text":"Ultraviolet did very little for it."},{"time":591680,"text":"Multispectral gave us everything."},{"time":594640,"text":"In Asia, we learned of monsters\nwith ears so long"},{"time":598240,"text":"that they could cover\nthe creature's entire body."},{"time":601040,"text":"In Africa, about a snake\nwho could cause the ground to smoke."},{"time":606680,"text":"Like starlight, which can convey images"},{"time":608960,"text":"of the way the Universe\nlooked in the distant past,"},{"time":611560,"text":"so multispectral light can take us back\nto the first stuttering moments"},{"time":615480,"text":"of an object's creation."},{"time":617480,"text":"Through this lens, we witness\nthe mistakes, the changes of mind,"},{"time":621440,"text":"the naïvetés, the uncensored thoughts,"},{"time":624360,"text":"the imperfections of the human imagination"},{"time":626600,"text":"that allow these hallowed objects\nand their authors"},{"time":629440,"text":"to become more real,"},{"time":631120,"text":"that make history closer to us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":634760,"text":"What about the future?"},{"time":636480,"text":"There's so much of the past,"},{"time":638680,"text":"and so few people\nwith the skills to rescue it"},{"time":641920,"text":"before these objects disappear forever."},{"time":646480,"text":"That's why I have begun to teach\nthis new hybrid discipline"},{"time":649800,"text":"that I call \"textual science.\""},{"time":651720,"text":"Textual science is a marriage"},{"time":653360,"text":"of the traditional skills\nof a literary scholar --"},{"time":655760,"text":"the ability to read old languages\nand old handwriting,"},{"time":658320,"text":"the knowledge of how texts are made"},{"time":660040,"text":"in order to be able\nto place and date them --"},{"time":662200,"text":"with new techniques like imaging science,"},{"time":664960,"text":"the chemistry of inks and pigments,"},{"time":667560,"text":"computer-aided optical\ncharacter recognition."}]},{"cues":[{"time":671160,"text":"Last year, a student in my class,"},{"time":673360,"text":"a freshman,"},{"time":674600,"text":"with a background in Latin and Greek,"},{"time":676440,"text":"was image-processing a palimpsest"},{"time":678800,"text":"that we had photographed\nat a famous library in Rome."},{"time":682240,"text":"As he worked, tiny Greek writing\nbegan to appear from behind the text."},{"time":688200,"text":"Everyone gathered around,"},{"time":689720,"text":"and he read a line from a lost work"},{"time":692400,"text":"of the Greek comic dramatist Menander."},{"time":695760,"text":"This was the first time\nin well over a thousand years"},{"time":698480,"text":"that those words\nhad been pronounced aloud."},{"time":701880,"text":"In that moment, he became a scholar."}]},{"cues":[{"time":705440,"text":"Ladies and gentlemen,\nthat is the future of the past."}]},{"cues":[{"time":708840,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":710080,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}